<br>
These are the tools of the trade, when it comes to druid healing in the end game.<br>
<br>
<b>Nature's Recovery: The New Regen</b><br>
Level 60, Luclin dropped spell<br>
900 hps healed in 3 minutes, for 250 mana<br>
30 hps/tick regen, stacks with Regrowth<br>
90 second recast delay<br>
3.6 hps/mana<br>
<br>
<b>Nature's Touch: Similar to Divine Light</b><br>
Level 60, Vendor spell<br>
880 hps healed for 400 mana<br>
5.5 second cast time<br>
no recast delay<br>
2.2 hps/mana<br>
<br>
<b>Chloroblast: Similar to Remedy</b><br>
Level 55, Vendor spell<br>
385 hps healed for 175 mana<br>
3 second cast time<br>
no recast delay<br>
2.2 hps/mana<br>
<br>
<b>Regrowth of the Grove: Group Regen</b><br>
Level 58, Kunark dropped spell<br>
15 hps/tick regen for 15 minutes for every party member<br>
600 mana<br>
22.5 hps/mana (maximum, however this is not often reached)<br>
<br>
Chloroblast and Nature's Touch both heal 2.2 hitpoints per mana.  Nature's Touch heals more hitpoints per unit time, and Chloroblast lands faster.<br>
<br>
Regrowth of the Grove and Nature's Recovery have good hp/mana ratios, but they are slow.  They are also relatively rare.  In high damage situations, they can only do part of the job.<br>
<br>
The recast delay on Nature's Recovery means it can only be used on 2 members of a party simultaneously.  In an AE situation, this leaves druids relying on direct heals to keep party members alive.  We can chain cast direct heals, but not for very long.  With a slight efficiency boost we could heal for another round or two.  Please take a look at just a few of the high efficiency alternatives available to clerics, paladins, necros (! yes.) and shamans.<br>
<br>
Complete Heal for 3k hps: 7.5 hps/mana<br>
Celestial Elixer: 5 hps/mana (HoT)<br>
Word of Restoration: 5 hps/mana (group)<br>
<br>
Healing Wave of Prexus: 6 hps/mana (group)<br>
<br>
3xPact of Shadow+Shadowbond+Vexing Mordinia: 2.67 hps/mana, 1100 damage to target, net loss of no life (assuming pact is reapplied immediately) ((group, HoT))<br>
<br>
Torpor: 6 hps/mana (group member only, side effects)<br>
Chloroblast: 2.2 hps/mana<br>
<br>
My point is, HoTs, Group Heals, and Complete heal are all very efficient heals that work in a relatively short amount of time (compared to regens).  Druids have none of these options.  The result is druids that run out of mana more quickly than their companions on a raid, when pushed to the limit of their healing abilities.  A few druids got tired of this (and a few other things), and decided to start a petition.  The rest is history.<br>
<br>
-Quelm, Hierophant<br>
