<br>
I'm reading 3.33:1 ratio on CE. (HoT 24 seconds)<br>
DivineLight: 2.6:1 ratio (+5%)<br>
WoR: 5:1 ratio (+5%) group<br>
Regrowth: 7.5:1<br>
Group Regrowth: 15:1 ratio<br>
Torpor: 6:1 ratio (30% slow &amp; a snare, HoT 24 seconds)<br>
So, some general rules.<br>
<br>
Group heals are 2x as efficient as normal heals.<br>
<br>
Direct heals are &lt; 2.6:1 ratio.<br>
<br>
NR: 3.6 ratio (3 minutes!, 1.5 minute RCT)<br>
NT: 2.2 ratio<br>
<br>
So, by this math, a group Druid heal would be 4.4 ratio, assuming NT:DL ratio is fair.<br>
<br>
Ie, 600 mana for a 440 HP group heal.<br>
<br>
NR is ... well, it is better than using NT all the time.<br>
<br>
If you dropped NR to a 1 minute HoT, and removed RCT, it would become +different+ from Torpor/CE.<br>
<br>
New NR: 3.6:1 ratio.  90 HPs per tick.  6.0 CT  1 minute duration.  900 HPs<br>
<br>
CE: 3.33:1 ratio.  300 HPs per tick.  4.0 CT   24 second duration.  1200 HPs.<br>
<br>
Torpor: 6:1 ratio.  300 HPs per tick.  Slow/Snare component.  6.0 CT  24 second duration.  1200 HPs<br>
<br>
These are truely compareable spells.  The old NR wasn't.<br>
<br>
So:<br>
Torpor &gt; New NR &gt; CE &gt; CHeal<br>
for casters and<br>
<br>
CHeal &gt; CE &gt; New NR &gt; Torpor<br>
for main tanks and<br>
<br>
Torpor &gt; New NR &gt; CE &gt; CHeal<br>
for downtime injured tanks<br>
<br>
CHeal &gt; Torpor &gt; New NR &gt; CE<br>
for downtime almost dead tanks<br>
<br>
New NR &gt; Torpor &gt;  CE &gt; CHeal<br>
for injured secondary tanks<br>
<br>
But really, there is no reason a Cleric can't get a variant on NR.  Tho, for a Cleric's sanity, I hope they'd get something like a PBAERoot, or a Lure-root, rather than more healing.<br>
